cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with computer vision applications, specifically superpixels and segmentation. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel structure and algorithm, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions medical image segmentation, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and image retrieval, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
